<div class="xar-mod-body">
    <img src="#xarTplGetImage('admin_generic.gif','base')#" class="xar-module-icon" alt="official icon" width="96" height="96" />

    <h2><xar:mlstring>Overview</xar:mlstring></h2>

    <h3><xar:mlstring>What is it?</xar:mlstring></h3>
        <p>
            <xar:mlstring>The XLink module is a utility module that allows you to establish relationships between module items and some independent identifier, e.g. for shortcut URLs or foreign key look-ups with external databases. Enable its hooks for any module where you want to use it...</xar:mlstring>
        </p>

    <h3><xar:mlstring>How to use it?</xar:mlstring></h3>
    <p><xar:mlstring>The independent identifier can be composed of a base name (optional) and an identifier.
        Examples : 200309121551.xyz, kbase 123, products "This Nice Product", ...</xar:mlstring></p>
    <p><xar:mlstring>For each hooked module, specify the acceptable base names for the items you want to reference.</xar:mlstring></p>
    <p><xar:mlstring>When you declare a base name as alias for short URLs, you can use index.php/kbase/123 instead of index.php/xlink/kbase/123
            </xar:mlstring></p>

    <h3><xar:mlstring>Included Blocks</xar:mlstring></h3>
        <p>
            <xar:mlstring>There are no included blocks.</xar:mlstring>
        </p>

    <h3><xar:mlstring>Included Hooks</xar:mlstring></h3>
        <p>
            <xar:mlstring>Hook Xlink to each module where you wish to enable the XLink module functionality.</xar:mlstring>
        </p>

